
[1]slightness

   SLIGHTNESS, n.

   1. Weakness; want of force or strength; superficialness; as the
   slightness of a wound or an impression.

   2. Negligence; want of attention; want of vehemence. How does it
   reproach the slightness of out sleepy heartless addresses!
